{
  "texts": [
    "Requirements elicitation occurs through stakeholder participation in an advanced requirement elicitation process with feature mapping and an explicit delivery model (Ebert et al. 2016; Jabbari et al. 2016).",
    "In short, we can say that DevOps places focus on the deployment of developed software, whether it is developed via Agile or other methodologies.",
    "DevOps also addresses gaps between developers and Information Technology (IT) operations / infrastructure, whilst Agile software development addresses communication gaps between endusers and developers.",
    "DevOps does not explicitly deal with cultural issues.",
    "The study of culture was traditionally mainly covered by sociologists and anthropologists until the 1980s (Inkeles and Levinson 1969; Kluckhohn and Strodtbeck 1961; Kroeger and Kluckholm 1952)."
  ]
}